# UI Design Standards

## Color Priority

- **ALWAYS use colors from `src/constants/colors.ts` first**
- Import: `import { colors } from '@/constants/colors'`
- Use predefined color classes: `colors.available.default`, `colors.selected.hover`, etc.
- Only use custom colors when not available in constants

### Color Usage Examples

#### ✅ Correct Usage

```tsx
// Import colors from constants
import { colors } from "@/constants/colors";

// Use colors in className with template literals
<span className={`${colors.highlightText.default} font-semibold`}>
  Highlighted text
</span>

// Use colors in conditional styling
<button className={`${colors.button.default} ${colors.button.hover}`}>
  Click me
</button>

// Use colors with additional classes
<div className={`${colors.available.default} ${colors.available.hover} rounded-lg`}>
  Available cell
</div>
```

#### ❌ Incorrect Usage

```tsx
// Don't hardcode colors
<span className="text-[#9dffbf] font-semibold">  // ❌ Hardcoded hex
<span className="text-green-500 font-semibold">  // ❌ Tailwind color

// Don't use colors without template literals
<span className={colors.highlightText.default}>  // ❌ Missing template literal

// Don't mix hardcoded and palette colors
<div className={`${colors.available.default} bg-red-200`}>  // ❌ Mixed approaches
```

#### Key Principles

1. **Always import colors**: `import { colors } from "@/constants/colors"`
2. **Use template literals**: `${colors.propertyName.variant}`
3. **Combine with other classes**: `${colors.button.default} ${colors.button.hover} rounded-lg`
4. **Follow the palette**: Use predefined colors instead of hardcoded values
5. **Maintain consistency**: All components should use the same color palette

## Component Standards

- **Use chadcn/ui components with New York style** (subtle shadows, compact sizing)
- Prefer Tailwind classes over custom CSS
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Maintain accessibility (ARIA, contrast, keyboard nav)

## File Structure

- UI components: `src/components/ui/`
- Custom components: `src/components/`
- Colors: `src/constants/colors.ts` (primary source)
